snippet: Bob Ladouceur, 58, the coach of De La Salle High School in Concord, Calif., is retiring after 34 years, ending a run that included a national-record 151-game winning streak from 1992 to 2003.
abstract: Bob Ladouceur, coach of the De La Salle High School football team in Concord, Calif, will retire after 34 years and a record 151-game winning streak from 1992 to 2003.
lead_paragraph: Bob Ladouceur, 58, the coach of De La Salle High School in Concord, Calif., is retiring after 34 years, ending a run that included a national-record 151-game winning streak from 1992 to 2003.

headline.main: Top High School Football Coach Retires
